<div class=WordSection1>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;line-height:normal'><b><span
lang=EN-US style='font-size:24.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Angina pectoris</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:18.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>What
is angina pectoris</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Angina pectoris is a clinical
syndrome manifested by pain, compression or discomfort in the region of the
heart against the background of a temporary violation of the circulation of the
heart muscle (myocardium).</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Angina attacks often develop
with physical or emotional stress.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>The disease is also known as</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>&quot;Angina pectoris&quot;;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>exertional angina;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>unstable angina.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>In English, the disease is
called:</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>angina pectoris;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>angina;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>coronary heart disease.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Causes</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>For a very long time,
atherosclerotic disease of the heart (coronary) arteries was considered the
cause of angina pectoris.&nbsp;Subsequently, the spasm of these arteries was
recognized as an “auxiliary”, functional mechanism of temporary circulatory
disorders (ischemia) of the myocardium and angina pectoris.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Who is at risk</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Consumers of chewing tobacco, smokers, including passive ones;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>suffering from diabetes mellitus, arterial hypertension, obesity;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>people with high levels of cholesterol or triglycerides in their
blood;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>patients whose relatives have coronary artery disease or have had
a heart attack;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>men over 45;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>women over 55;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>leading an inactive lifestyle;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>those who experience a state of increased stress, emotional
outbursts.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>How often does it occur</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>The prevalence of angina in
Western countries is estimated to be 30,000 to 40,000 cases per million and
increases with age in both sexes.&nbsp;Among women, it affects from 5-7% at the
age of 45-64 to 10-12% at the age of 65-84, and among men - from 4-7% at the
age of 45-64 to 14-15% at the age of 65 -84 years old.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>The incidence and prevalence
of patients with angina pectoris is expected to increase in the coming decade
as a result of an aging population, an obesity epidemic and other risk factors.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Classification</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>There are the following types
of angina pectoris&nbsp;</span></b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>:</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Stable - the provoking factors are physical and emotional stress,
the attack lasts 5-15 minutes, is stopped by medicine or rest;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>unstable - attacks occur spontaneously, pain lasts more than 15
minutes and does not completely stop;&nbsp;often precedes myocardial
infarction, rhythm disturbances, or sudden death;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>variant (Prinzmetal's angina) - pain attacks occur at rest at the
same time of day, last more than 15 minutes and are accompanied by transient
changes in the ECG;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>microvascular (syndrome X) - a condition in which there are signs
of myocardial ischemia and spasm of the epicardial coronary arteries on
coronary angiography, but there is no atherosclerosis.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Classification of the severity
of stable angina pectoris by functional class according to the Canadian
Cardiovascular Society&nbsp;</span></b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>:</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>class I - normal activity does not cause an attack - pain occurs
with intense and fast or prolonged exertion;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>class II - a slight restriction of normal activity - angina
pectoris appears when walking quickly or climbing stairs, uphill, after eating,
in cold weather, with emotional stress and in the first hours after waking up;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>class III - a pronounced restriction of normal physical activity -
angina pectoris occurs when walking calmly a distance of one or two blocks on
flat terrain or climbing one flight of stairs at a normal pace under normal
conditions;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>class IV - inability to exercise without discomfort - angina
attacks can occur at rest.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Symptoms</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>The attack&nbsp;</span></b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>appears&nbsp;<b>suddenly&nbsp;</b>with
physical exertion;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>pain behind the sternum&nbsp;</span></b><span style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>or in the region of the
heart of a pressing, burning, aching character;&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>irradiation (spread) of pain&nbsp;</span></b><span
style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>to the
left shoulder or arm to the fingertips;&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>sensation&nbsp;<b>of squeezing&nbsp;</b>or&nbsp;<b>tightness&nbsp;</b>in
the chest;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>shortness of breath&nbsp;</span></b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>feeling of&nbsp;<b>fear&nbsp;</b>;&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>nausea, vomiting&nbsp;</span></b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Diagnosis of the disease</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Questioning and inspection</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>The patient is interviewed
about the pain syndrome in the chest, its nature, the frequency of occurrence
and the circumstances in which it disappears.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>During examination and
examination, measurements of height and weight, blood pressure according to
Korotkov, heart rate and pulse, palpation of the pulse on the radial and
arteries of the dorsum of the feet, auscultation of the heart and lungs,
examining the skin, identifies signs of risk factors (obesity, diabetes
mellitus, atherosclerosis, arterial hypertension).</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Laboratory examination</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Study of the lipid spectrum of blood, including low density
lipoprotein cholesterol;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>clinical blood test;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>determination of the level of blood glucose, glycated hemoglobin;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>study of blood creatinine levels.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Functional, radiation and
instrumental diagnostics</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Electrocardiography;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>stress test;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>echocardiography;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>nuclear perfusion imaging of the myocardium (nuclear stress test);</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>coronary angiography;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>chest x-ray;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>computed tomography of the heart;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>magnetic resonance imaging of the heart.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Treatment</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Treatment goals</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Relief of acute symptoms;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>prevention of complications;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>reduction of ischemia.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Lifestyle and aids</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>They matter as methods of prevention,
not treatment.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Medications</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>The presented drugs can be
used as monotherapy or in combination:</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>nitrates&nbsp;</span></b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>help to relax and dilate blood
vessels;&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>antiplatelet drugs&nbsp;</span></b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>block platelet
aggregation;&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Beta blockers&nbsp;</span></b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>improve blood flow and oxygen
delivery by lowering heart rate and blood pressure&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>calcium channel blockers&nbsp;</span></b><span style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>inhibit calcium
transport and induce smooth muscle relaxation;&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>a sodium channel blocker (ranolazine)&nbsp;</span></b><span
style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>reduces
the intracellular ionic balance during ischemia;&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>statins&nbsp;</span></b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>lower blood cholesterol levels;&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>an If channel inhibitor&nbsp;</span></b><span style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>regulates the heart
rate.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Surgical operations</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>With the ineffectiveness of
drug treatment, the presence of signs of damage to the coronary bed and a
decrease in the quality of life, revascularization (using percutaneous coronary
intervention) or coronary artery bypass grafting is indicated.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Recovery and improvement of
the quality of life</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Cardiac rehabilitation
programs for angina pectoris have not been developed.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Possible complications</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Unstable angina;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>myocardial infarction;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>chronic heart failure;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>heart rhythm disorder;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>sudden death.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Prophylaxis</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Lifestyle: adequate physical activity in conjunction with the
exercise therapy doctor, proper nutrition (food with less animal fat,
vegetables and fruits, complex carbohydrates, dietary fiber, fish), stress
control;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>regularly monitor the pulse and blood pressure;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>exclude smoking.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Forecast</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Important prognostic
indicators in patients with angina pectoris: left ventricular function,
localization and severity of atherosclerotic lesions, and response to
treatment.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Patients with angina pectoris
have impaired ability to carry out daily activities.&nbsp;It is necessary to
take this into account when deciding on the performance of certain everyday or
professional tasks.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>What questions should you ask
your doctor</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>If the ECG result showed no abnormalities, then I am healthy?</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
